---
import { BannerDemo } from '../../components/BannerDemo';
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Banner" description="Groundwork banner component">
  <section class="gw-section">
    <div class="gw-width gw-stack--lg">
      <div class="gw-prose">
        <h1 class="gw-heading-l">Banner</h1>
        <p>Use Banner for important page-level messages that users should notice before continuing.</p>
        <h2 class="gw-heading-m">When to use</h2>
        <p>Use Banner for confirmations, warnings, errors, and neutral notices. Every banner has a visible title so the message is clear without relying on colour alone.</p>
        <h2 class="gw-heading-m">When not to use</h2>
        <p>Do not use Banner for inline form validation; use Field errors and ErrorSummary. Do not use it for decorative callouts or low-priority marketing content.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="gw-card gw-stack">
        <h2 class="gw-heading-m">Demo</h2>
        <BannerDemo />
      </div>

      <div class="gw-card gw-stack">
        <h2 class="gw-heading-m">Accessibility notes</h2>
        <p class="gw-body--sm">Banner requires a visible title. The title gives the message a non-colour cue, while the variant adds supporting visual emphasis.</p>
        <p class="gw-body--sm">Static banners should not announce themselves by default. Use <code class="gw-mono">announcement="polite"</code> for dynamically inserted status messages and <code class="gw-mono">announcement="assertive"</code> only for urgent messages that need immediate attention.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
